{"id": 38, "ts": 1778868075.7287607, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "After reviewing all the documented attributes for each candidate, the picture is clear:\n- **Candidate\u202fA** shows strong technical vision and leadership, but we have no evidence of reliability, calmness under pressure, or teamwork/communication. The noted resistance to new ideas and \u201cshow\u2011off\u201d attitude further weaken his fit for a crew\u2011centric, high\u2011stress environment.\n- **Candidate\u202fB** is the only candidate with explicit **100\u202f% reliability** and a proven ability to **stay calm in a crisis**\u2014the two most critical safety factors for long\u2011distance operations. He also brings solid technical competence (weather assessment, computer skills). The only recorded drawbacks are interpersonal: a weak memory for numbers, occasional harsh remarks, and sometimes using the wrong tone. While these are concerns for crew harmony, they do not directly compromise the core safety and reliability requirements.\n- **Candidate\u202fC** excels in quick, correct decision\u2011making, is very conscientious, understands complex technology, and even creates a positive atmosphere with his crew, indicating good teamwork. However, we lack any reliability attribute, and his difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric stance, and lack of willingness to pursue further education raise serious doubts about consistent performance and long\u2011term development.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** demonstrates responsibility (takes it seriously) and strong problem\u2011solving and concentration skills, and he responds to unexpected events **adequately**. Yet his calmness is only \u201cadequate,\u201d and his hot temper, arrogant/know\u2011it\u2011all demeanor, and the absence of any documented teamwork or communication strengths make him a riskier choice for the collaborative, high\u2011pressure nature of long\u2011haul flights.\nBalancing the selection criteria, **Candidate\u202fB** uniquely satisfies the essential safety pillars\u2014full reliability, proven calmness under pressure, and solid technical ability\u2014while his interpersonal issues, though notable, are less detrimental than the fundamental gaps seen in the other candidates. Therefore, I support **Candidate\u202fB** for the long\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
