{"id": 42, "ts": 1778868089.971405, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 2, "agent": "agent_3", "message": "From the complete set of documented attributes, Candidate\u202fB is the only pilot with explicit evidence of both **100\u202f% reliability** and the ability to **stay calm in a crisis**\u2014the two most critical safety factors for long\u2011distance, high\u2011responsibility flights. He also brings solid technical competence (weather assessment, computer skills) that supports international route planning and navigation.\nAll other candidates lack at least one of these core safety attributes:\n* **Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 strong technical vision and leadership, but no documented reliability, calmness under pressure, or teamwork/communication.\n* **Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 quick, correct decision\u2011making and a concern for others, yet no reliability attribute and no explicit calm\u2011under\u2011pressure evidence; communication difficulties and lack of willingness to develop further raise concerns for crew cohesion and long\u2011term growth.\n* **Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 reliable in the sense of taking responsibility and solving problems, but his calmness is only described as \u201cadequate,\u201d and there is no evidence of effective teamwork or communication; moodiness and a loner reputation further weaken his crew\u2011interaction profile.\nGiven that reliability and calmness under pressure are non\u2011negotiable for safe long\u2011haul operations, Candidate\u202fB best satisfies the essential criteria despite noted interpersonal shortcomings, which are less critical than the missing safety fundamentals in the other applicants.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}"}
